Again they are mentioned as wall-shields, of which kind a curious specimen formed ofiron is preserved in the porter’s lodge at VVarwick castle. “ It nedethe bat ther be good plentie of targes, pauysses, and sheldes in be citie, to keuer and to hin or stop the gappes of the enbatil- mentes of be walles fro shot.'⁷ B. iv. 0. 6. They are also mentioned as useful in sea- fights.
